tt-local-generator (0.2.5) noble; urgency=medium

  * Timestamps: store all created_at fields in UTC (ISO 8601 with +00:00
    offset); display in the user's local timezone using 12-hour format
    (e.g. "May 7  8:33 AM").  New time_utils module provides utc_now_iso(),
    fmt_local_12h(), fmt_local_date(), fmt_local_time() — all callers updated.
    Legacy naive timestamps (no timezone suffix) treated as UTC for backward
    compatibility with existing records.

